NKPC Persistence Data

Preliminaries

We need to set up the two packages used - you may need to install them first.

library(tidyverse)
library(DataCombine)

We import the BLS datasets for mining and logging, durables manufacturing and non-durables manufacturing.

base_minelog <- read.table("https://download.bls.gov/pub/time.series/ce/ce.data.10a.MiningAndLogging.Employment", header = TRUE, sep = "", fill = TRUE)
base_durables <- read.table("https://download.bls.gov/pub/time.series/ce/ce.data.31a.ManufacturingDurableGoods.Employment", header = TRUE, sep = "", fill = TRUE)
base_nondurables <- read.table("https://download.bls.gov/pub/time.series/ce/ce.data.32a.ManufacturingNondurableGoods.Employment", header = TRUE, sep = "", fill = TRUE)

We pick the necessary time series i.e. the monthly data on “all employees in thousands”. These are the chosen time series with a CES prefix and 01 suffix.

minelog <- subset(base_minelog, series_id == "CES1021100001" | series_id == "CES1021200001" | series_id == "CES1021300001" | series_id == "CES1011330001", select=c(series_id, year, period, value))

durables <- subset(base_durables, series_id == "CES3132100001" | series_id == "CES3132700001" | series_id == "CES3133100001" | series_id == "CES3133200001" | series_id == "CES3133300001" | series_id == "CES3133400001" | series_id == "CES3133500001" | series_id == "CES3133600001" | series_id == "CES3133700001" | series_id == "CES3133900001", select=c(series_id, year, period, value))

nondurables <- subset(base_nondurables, series_id == "CES3231100001" | series_id == "CES3231300001" | series_id == "CES3231400001" | series_id == "CES3231500001" | series_id == "CES3232200001" | series_id == "CES3232300001" | series_id == "CES3232400001" | series_id == "CES3232500001" | series_id == "CES3232600001" | series_id == "CES3232900001", select=c(series_id, year, period, value))

We then convert the months into numbers.

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){sector$period <- gsub("M", "", sector$period) %>% as.numeric(sector$period)})

minelog$period <- res[[1]]
durables$period <- res[[2]]
nondurables$period <- res[[3]]

Then we aggregate the data into quarterly data.

minelog$day <- rep(1,times=2232)
durables$day <- rep(1,times=4218)
nondurables$day <- rep(1,times=3750)

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){as.Date(paste(sector$year, sector$period, sector$day, sep="-"), "%Y-%m-%d")})

minelog$date <- res[[1]]
durables$date <- res[[2]]
nondurables$date <- res[[3]]

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){quarters(sector$date)})

minelog$quarter <- res[[1]]
durables$quarter <- res[[2]]
nondurables$quarter <- res[[3]]

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){aggregate(value ~ series_id + quarter + year, sector, sum)})

minelog <- res[[1]]
durables <- res[[2]]
nondurables <- res[[3]]

Setting Up Variables of Interest

We take the natural logs of employment.

minelog$logemp <- log(minelog$value)
durables$logemp <- log(durables$value)
nondurables$logemp <- log(nondurables$value)

We restrict the sample to between 1990 and 2019.

minelog <- minelog[minelog$year > 1989 & minelog$year < 2020,]
durables <- durables[durables$year > 1989 & durables$year < 2020,]
nondurables <- nondurables[nondurables$year > 1989 & nondurables$year < 2020,]

We find the differences in log employment for 4, 12 and 20 quarters i.e. the growth rate of employment.

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){sector %>% group_by(series_id) %>% mutate(logemp - lag(logemp, n = 4))})
minelog$fourth <- res[[1]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 4)`
durables$fourth <- res[[2]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 4)`
nondurables$fourth <- res[[3]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 4)`

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){sector %>% group_by(series_id) %>% mutate(logemp - lag(logemp, n = 12))})
minelog$twelth <- res[[1]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 12)`
durables$twelth <- res[[2]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 12)`
nondurables$twelth <- res[[3]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 12)`

dflist <- list(minelog, durables, nondurables)
res <- lapply(dflist, function(sector){sector %>% group_by(series_id) %>% mutate(logemp - lag(logemp, n = 20))})
minelog$twentieth <- res[[1]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 20)`
durables$twentieth <- res[[2]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 20)`
nondurables$twentieth <- res[[3]]$`logemp - lag(logemp, n = 20)`

Regressions

We regress the 4th/12th/20th difference of log employment by each mining/logging series against its 1st lag.

ml_d4l1 <- by(data = minelog, minelog$series_id, function(subset){lm(fourth ~ lag(fourth), subset)}) %>% sapply(., coef) %>% as.data.frame(.,row.names = c("Intercept","D4L1")) %>% .[-1,1:4] %>% pivot_longer(c("CES1021100001","CES1021200001","CES1021300001","CES1011330001"), names_to = "series", values_to = "D4L1")

ml_d12l1 <- by(data = minelog, minelog$series_id, function(subset){lm(twelth ~ lag(twelth), subset)}) %>% sapply(., coef) %>% as.data.frame(.,row.names = c("Intercept","D12L1")) %>% .[-1,1:4] %>% pivot_longer(c("CES1021100001","CES1021200001","CES1021300001","CES1011330001"), names_to = "series", values_to = "D12L1")

ml_d20l1 <- by(data = minelog, minelog$series_id, function(subset){lm(twentieth ~ lag(twentieth), subset)}) %>% sapply(., coef) %>% as.data.frame(.,row.names = c("Intercept","D20L1")) %>% .[-1,1:4] %>% pivot_longer(c("CES1021100001","CES1021200001","CES1021300001","CES1011330001"), names_to = "series", values_to = "D20L1")

Aggregation of Data

We aggregate all the regression coefficients.

mlcoefs <- merge(ml_d4l1, ml_d4l4)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d4l8)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d12l1)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d12l4)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d12l8)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d20l1)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d20l4)
mlcoefs <- merge(mlcoefs, ml_d20l8)
mlcoefs <- bind_cols(mlcoefs,c(rep("minelog",4))) %>% rename(sector = ...11)
## New names:
## * NA -> ...11
dcoefs <- merge(d_d4l1, d_d4l4)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d4l8)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d12l1)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d12l4)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d12l8)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d20l1)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d20l4)
dcoefs <- merge(dcoefs, d_d20l8)
dcoefs <- bind_cols(dcoefs,c(rep("durables",10))) %>% rename(sector = ...11)
## New names:
## * NA -> ...11
ndcoefs <- merge(nd_d4l1, nd_d4l4)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d4l8)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d12l1)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d12l4)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d12l8)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d20l1)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d20l4)
ndcoefs <- merge(ndcoefs, nd_d20l8)
ndcoefs <- bind_cols(ndcoefs,c(rep("nondurables",10))) %>% rename(sector = ...11)
## New names:
## * NA -> ...11
allcoefs <- bind_rows(dcoefs, ndcoefs)
allcoefs <- bind_rows(allcoefs, mlcoefs)

We replace the series_id with two digit codes which are easier to read.

replaceData <- data.frame(from = c("CES1021100001", "CES1021200001", "CES1021300001", "CES1011330001","CES3132100001", "CES3132700001", "CES3133100001", "CES3133200001", "CES3133300001", "CES3133400001", "CES3133500001", "CES3133600001", "CES3133700001", "CES3133900001","CES3231100001", "CES3231300001", "CES3231400001", "CES3231500001", "CES3232200001", "CES3232300001", "CES3232400001", "CES3232500001", "CES3232600001", "CES3232900001"), to = c("OG","MX","SM","LG","WD","NM","PM","FM","MC","CE","EE","TR","FN","MD","FO","TX","TP","AP","PP","PR","PT","CH","PL","MN"))

allcoefs <- FindReplace(data = allcoefs, Var = "series", replaceData, from = "from", to = "to")
## Only exact matches will be replaced.
allcoefs2 <- allcoefs %>% pivot_longer(c("D4L1","D4L4","D4L8","D12L1","D12L4","D12L8","D20L1","D20L4","D20L8"), names_to = "measure", values_to = "persistence")
